- Scikit-learn  
- Google Colab  

ğŸ“Š Key Analysis Performed  
- Data cleaning and text preprocessing (tokenization, stopword removal, lemmatization)  
- Sentiment distribution visualization  
- WordClouds for each sentiment class  
- TF-IDF vectorization of tweet text  
- Logistic Regression model to classify sentiment  
- Confusion matrix and classification report  
- Time-series plot of sentiment trends over time  
- Optional: Sentiment trends per airline  

ğŸ” Key Insights  
ğŸ’¬ Majority of tweets are negative, showing customer dissatisfaction trends.  
ğŸ“… Sentiment trends reveal peaks in negative tweets on specific dates (e.g., service disruptions).  
âœˆï¸ Airlines like United and American have a higher ratio of negative feedback.  
ğŸ“ˆ The Logistic Regression model performs well in identifying sentiment with good precision and recall.
